<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23524] Big local shuffle blocks should not be checked for corruption.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23524</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In current code, all local blocks will be checked for corruption no matter it&apos;s big or not.&#160; The reasons are as below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Size in FetchResult for local block is set to be 0 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/storage/ShuffleBlockFetcherIterator.scala#L327)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/storage/ShuffleBlockFetcherIterator.scala#L327)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4105&quot; title=&quot;FAILED_TO_UNCOMPRESS(5) errors when fetching shuffle data with sort-based shuffle&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-4105&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-4105&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; meant to only check the small blocks(size&amp;lt;maxBytesInFlight/3), but for reason 1, below check will be invalid. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/storage/ShuffleBlockFetcherIterator.scala#L420&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/storage/ShuffleBlockFetcherIterator.scala#L420&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
